# **Capstone Project Part 2: Backend Design**

**Project Title:** The AI Mood-Jockey

## **1\. Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)![][image1]**

### **Entity Descriptions:**

* **User:** Stores authentication details (username, email, password) to allow personalized playlist history.  
* **Mood\_Query:** Captures the user's natural language input and the structured keywords/parameters extracted by the Gemini AI.  
* **Track:** A local cache of music metadata retrieved from Jamendo (title, artist, preview URL) to ensure fast loading of history.  
* **Playlist\_Track:** A junction table that links specific tracks to the mood query that generated them, allowing for a many-to-many relationship.

## **2\. API Endpoints**

The backend is structured into two main Django applications: `web_interface` and `playlist_generator`.

### **A. Web Interface (Frontend Views)**

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| GET | / | Renders the main dashboard where users can enter their mood text. |
| GET | /history/ | Renders a page displaying all past mood-to-music queries for the user. |

### **B. Playlist Generator (Backend API)**

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Data Handling |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| POST | /generate/ | The core engine. It sends the user input to Gemini, parses the genres/moods/tags, fetches tracks from Jamendo, and saves the result. | **Input:** `{ "user_input": "string" }` **Output:** Redirects to results or returns JSON track list. |
| GET | /api/query/\<int:id\>/ | Retrieves details for a specific historical search. | **Output:** JSON object with query details and associated tracks. |
| DELETE | /api/query/\<int:id\>/ | Allows users to remove a specific search from their history. | **Action:** Deletes query and associated playlist links. |

### **C. Authentication (User Management)**

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| POST | /login/ | Authenticates user and starts session. |
| POST | /register/ | Creates a new user account. |
| GET | /logout/ | Ends the user session. |
